Subject:    MB and MR records
From:       <a href="?a=95837817200021&r=1&w=2">mcsun!ukc!cam-eng!jmrm () uunet ! uu ! net  (James Matheson)</a>
Date:       <a href="?l=namedroppers&r=1&w=2&b=199006">1990-06-05 10:37:16</a></font>
[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837797327036&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837797327036&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

I would like to be able to use information from the nameserver to cause
the rewriting of addresses within sendmail so that mail addressed to
machines which do not run a sendmail daemon can be readdressed to the
appropriate machine.

Do either MB or MR records provide an appropriate basis for doing this
(the only info I can find is in RFC 1035 and this is rather brief)?

Are either/both of these likely to be adopted as standard RRs rather
than experimental?

james

